The §f§2Sieve§f is the main source of resources in this pack, but don't worry, it can be automated as soon as you get into the steam age!

§2§fRight-Click the §2Sieve§f with an §2Mesh§f to put it in and then hold Right-Click with the block you want to sift, for example§2 Dirt§f to get the resources you want from this block.

§2Sieves§f can be put nearby each other to sift multiple blocks at once! Pretty neat, or?
Like in almost any other modpacks, you will begin with punching trees to get wood, except this time in the sky and with no exploration needed.

As mentioned in the welcome quest, this modpack features §2Effortless Building§f!

§2Effortless Building§f makes building by a thousand times easier by allowing to build simple structures like floors and walls in an limited range that can be upgraded with §2Range Upgrades§f which you can acquire while progressing.

To access the menu of the mod, press and hold §2ALT§f.

This modpack also features an mod called §2Twerk-Sim 2K16§f!

This mod allows you to grow an sapling without bonemeal by spamming crouch near it.

This Modpack features §2OreExcavation§f!

§2OreExcavation§f allows to mine all blocks of the same type §2at once§f when holding down the button assigned to it (standard assigned to §8§2grave§f, can be changed in controls).

Useful, or?

Breaking §2§2Leaves§f with an §2Crook §fwill increase the overall chance of their drops and allows to obtain an special item called §f§2Silkworm§f.

§2§fRight-Clicking §f§2Leaves§f with an §1§2Silkworm§f will turn them into §2Infested Leaves§f, wait till their "infestation" is done and break them with an §2Crook§f to obtain lots of §2String§f!

Getting an §2Barrel §fwill allow you getting §2dirt§f by putting compostables in like §2saplings §fwhich can be looked up in JEI.

It also allows various§2 fluid transformations§f for different kinds of materials like §2soul sand§f, just right click the barrel in JEI to see what's possible with it!

Getting an §2Crucible§f out of wood will allow you to obtain early §2Water §fin this pack and right-clicking it with §2Dust§k§f while it's filled with §2Water§f will allow you to obtain early §f§3§3§2Clay§f.

Don't forget to make your 2x2 infinite water source, so you don't have to do this everytime you want water!

Welcome to §2Gregtech: Skybound§f!

§2Gregtech: Skybound§f is an lightweight skyblock modpack focussing mainly around §2Gregtech CE: Unofficial§f with some QoL and utility mods like §2Applied Energistics 2§f or §2Effortless building§f!

These Quests here will try to teach you through the early progression of this modpack and of Gregtech.

Hope you enjoy this pack!
The §2Hammer§f allows you to grind down various blocks, like §2Cobblestone§f into §3§2Gravel§f, §2Gravel§f into §2Sand§f, and so on.
It's finally time to craft an §2Furnace§f! No funny description this time.

The §2Clay Bucket§f is the earliest way of transferring Fluids like §2Water§f.
Note that it will break when transferring §2Lava§f!

The §2Crucible§f made out of §2Bricks§f will allow you to obtain §2Lava§f easily by putting any Stones in it when an appropiate heat source like an §2Torch§f is under it. 
Be sure to check JEI which stone yields the most §2Lava§!!

§2Witch Water§e§f is an very useful fluid early and can be used to create as example an endless §2Dirt§f or §2Stone§f generator that generates all types of Stone!

To obtain §2Witch Water§f, use the §2Ancient Spores§f you obtained by sifting §2Dirt§f earlier on an 3x3 §2Dirt§f field by clicking on the middle block to transform it to §2Mycelium§f. Place an §2Barrel §fwith §2Water§a§f in it and it will begin slowly to transform into §2Witch Water§f! Note that this process also generates§2 Mushrooms§f.

As mentioned in an earlier quest, §2Witch Water§f allows you to make an unlimited §2Stone§f generator that generates any type of Stone! 

Just like in an normal Cobblestone generator, let the §2Lava§f flow to the §2Witchwater§f to create Stones. 

Different stream lengths of the §2Witch Water§f will create different §3§2Stones§f as followed:

1 Block - §2Diorite
§f2-3 Blocks - §2Granite
§f4-7 Blocks - §2Andesite

As mentioned in the earlier quest, you can make with§2 Witch Water§f an generator that generates endless §2Dirt§f. You can do that by making an simple Cobblestone generator but instead of §2Lava§f you use §2Witch water§f! §k§k§k

Flint Tools are the first GT Tools available in this pack and have fairly decent durability.

Some Tools have an unique feature compared to their vanilla versions, for example will the §2Axe§f cut down a whole tree instead of needing to break every single log, or the §2Pickaxe§f will place §2Torches§f when Right-Clicking a block.

Now that you have obtained all kinds of Stones, it's time to actually obtain some important resources like §f§2Iron§k§f or §2Copper§f!

Here won't be listed where to obtain which resource, so please look up in JEI where to obtain which ore!

Gregtech also has Tools that are mainly used for Crafting like the §a§3§2Hammer §for §2File§e.

§fThose will be used ALOT in the progression, but don't worry, you can later on make items like §2Plates §fand §2Screws §fin machines so you don't have to make it by hand all the time.

NOTE: This quest accepts either§2 Wrought Iron§f or §2Iron §ftools.
Finally, an real Bucket.

§2Wrought Iron§f is an very durable tool material early on, it has the double durability of §2Iron§f and is very easy to make.

§k§l§fIt's made by putting§2 Iron Nuggets§f in an §2Furnace§  and combining the §foutcoming §2Wrought Iron Nuggets§f into an §2Wrought Iron Ingot§f.

§2Bronze§f is an important alloy made out of §2Tin§f and§2 Copper§f that will be needed to get into the§e Steam Age§f!

It is made by combining §2§f3 §2Copper dust§f and 1 §2§2Tin dust§f in an crafting table and smelting the outcoming §2Bronze dust §fin an §2Furnace§f.

The §2Bronze Mesh§f is the next tier Mesh, allowing to obtain new materials like §2Redstone§f or §2Silver§f. 

These materials will be important in the later progression.

The §2Block Breaker§f will automatically break blocks in front of it. It can be used to easily automate the generators you already built up.

It's working state can be easily toggled with an lever.

As you may have noticed, §2Charcoal§f cannot be made in an §2Furnace§f, you need to make it in an §2Coke Oven§f.

The §2Coke Oven§f§f is the first Multiblock you can make in this Pack, it's 3x3x3 and hollow in the middle.

It's the early way of obtaining §2Charcoal§f and gives as byproduct§2 Creosote§f, which can be used to make §2Treated Wood§f that will become handy later on.

The §2Hatches§f allow for basic automation with hoppers, pipes, etc. They can output both §2Creosote §fand §2Charcoal§f and allow inputting §2Wood§f.

It also accepts §2Coal§f, and will output an more powerful fuel called §2Coke§f!

Getting an §2Solid Fuel Steam Boiler§f will bring you torwards §eAge 0 - The Steam Age§f!

Simply just put §2Water§f into the §2Boiler§f and then put an burnable fuel in like §2Coal§f§f and wait for it to build up heat by watching the red bar going up, then it will begin to produce §2Steam§f! It won't output §2Steam§f to the bottom, it's the best to use that side to input §2Water§f from that side (It was specifically implemented for this).

§fNOTE: Never put §2Water§f into the §2Boiler§f while it's hot and empty, else it will explode!

Welcome to §eAge 0 - The Steam Age§f! While you don't have electricity yet, you can make Steam Machines now, which will help you out alot early.

Hint: You can turn off Machines - both Electric and Steam ones - with an §2Soft Mallet§f, so if your Steam Machine ran out of §2Steam§f, be sure to turn it off and turn it back on as soon as the §2Boiler §fmade more!

The §2Primitive Pump§f is an Multiblock that produces water infinitely, but is limited in how much it produces per second.

It depends on the Biome on how much it produces, for example building it in an  Ocean/River Biome will make it produce 1000L/s.

NOTE: Compared to the other Multiblocks, this one needs to be built EXACTLY like the Preview in JEI.

In Gregtech, Fluid and Item transportation is done using §3§2Pipes§f.
§3§2Pipes§f are the only way nearby an ME-System to transfer Items and Fluids around in this pack.

§2Pipes§f will not auto-extract Fluids/Items from Blocks, you need to use something that can do that like §2Hoppers §f(There's an version out of wood in this pack), or §2Covers§f (Those will be shown in an later quest).

Each Pipe has different transfer rates, depending on the Material they are made. The bests you can make right now are §2Tin §fand§2 Bronze§f ones.

You can see in their description which can transfer Items and which can transfer Fluids, it also depends on the Material.

NOTE: Output Hatches and Buses from Multiblocks will auto-insert into Pipes, but be sure that the output face is showing where the Pipe is, else it won't auto-insert!
A §2Stone Barrel§a§f is used to obtain things like §2Obsidian§f or §2Netherrack§f, because those require that §L§2Lava §fis in the Barrel and the Wooden one cannot take it.

The §2§2Alloy Smelter§f is the first Steam Machine you should make, as it allows to make all Alloys you will need in this Age and the next. 

It also allows you to make easier §2Bronze§f, because it gives you 4 instead of only 3 and doesn't need dust to alloy it together.
The§2 Steam Macerator§f allows you to easily grind down Items and Blocks with Steam, no more needing a mortar to grind down stuff!

Ore Processing in Gregtech will double the output and if done complete will give some neat byproducts, but with the current machines it's way too slow to do. 
So you should ignore it before§e Age 3 (High Voltage)§f§,, because the amount of ores you get at this moment will last you for a while without doubling it.

The§2§2§2 Steam Sieve§f can perform sifting recipes, allowing you to easily automate sifting. No more hours of right-clicking!

NOTE: You should get an better infrastructure before trying to do full automation, one boiler will not be enough!

The §2Steam Grinder§f and§2 § §2Steam Oven §fare very powerful multiblocks that §fcan process 8 Items and once, but only take 1.5x of the time it needs normally! 
Time to replace those slow ass Steam Machines!

Note: In quests like this one, only either task need to be done, not both!
§2Potin§f is an very powerful material for §2Fluid Pipes§,, it has the best stats §ffor those in this Age and will be used still alot later too.

The §2Rock Breaker§f allows you to generate pretty fast any type of stone, faster than your current generator! 
But note that it only can generate one type of Stone that you want it to generate.
As the name says, the§2 Steam Compressor§f allows you to compress things with the power of Steam! It is needed to progress further, so you definitely should make it.
The §2Steam Furnace§k§f§f allows you to cook Items with Steam instead of needing to feed it everytime with solid fuels.

The§2 Primitive Blast Furnace§f is one of the main goals in this Age and is an important step getting towards §eAge 1 - Low Voltage§f!

With either some §2Coal§f, §2Coke§f or §2Charcoal§f and §2Iron §for §2Wrought Iron§f§f you will be finally able to get some §2Steel§f!§2 Wrought Iron§f will process faster into§2 Steel§f than normal §2Iron§f.

The§2 Forge Hammer§f allows you to make §2§f2 § Plates with only 3 Ingots and a bit of Steam, saving alot of material early! 
It reflects all Ex Nihilo §2Hammer§f recipes too.

High Pressure Steam Machines are faster versions of the normal Steam Machines and are as fast as Low Voltage Machines! 
These will halve the time it'll need to process things for all Machines, but will consume more steam too!
The next thing you should make are §2Molds§k§k§f. Those are important to progress further and allow you to §fmake §2Glass§f,§2 Rubber §fand §2Vacuum Tubes§f.

The §2Steam Solar Boiler§f allows you to produce §3§2Steam§f with only §2Water§f and Sunlight!

NOTE: The High Pressure variant will produce the double amount of §2Steam §fcompared to the normal one!

The §2Steam Liquid Boiler§f allows you to produce lots of §2Steam§f with either §2Creosote§f or §2Lava§k§f as Fuel.

NOTE: The High Pressure variant will produce the double amount of §2Steam §fcompared to the normal one!

§2Netherrack§f§f§f will allow you to obtain §2Sulfur§f, which is an important ingredient to obtain§2 Rubber§f.

It is obtained by right-clicking an §2Stone Barrel§f§f filled with §2Lava§f with§2 Redstone§f. It can be automated using§2 Item Pipes§f too!
Obtaining §2Rubber§f is an important step towards§2§e Age 1 - Low Voltage§f as it allows you to make cables and is used in alot of other recipes.

§2Covers §fare extremly powerful in what they can do, but for now we will only focus on those for the §2Item and Fluid Pipes§f.

The§2 Robot Arm§f allows you to extract and insert items from any Block that has an inventory, it's speed is determined by the tier you have crafted. You can see on the Tooltip how much it can transfer.

The§3§2 Pump§f is similar to the §1§2Robot Arm§f, just for Fluids instead of Items.

Those should help you alot out in getting decent automation finally!

§2Vacuum Tubes§f are one of the ingredients needed for your first §2LV Circuits§f! 

I'd recommend to batch-craft already components, as you will need lots of §2Circuits§f for Machines and such.
The§2 Resistors§f are the next Circuit part you should craft, be sure to go the §2Fine Copper Wire§f route for crafting, as it will allow you to safe resources!
The §2Basic Circuit Board §fis the last part you need for your first §2LV Circuits§f.

The§2 Steam Extractor§f will be needed to obtain §2Raw Rubber§f, which can be processed down together with§2 Sulfur§9§f into §2Rubber§f.§2 §f
Put some §2Sticky Resin §f it and it should begin to process it, note that it will take some time to process!

§2Sticky Resin§f, when processed is used for making §2Rubber§f which is an important material that you will need lots of by now!

It is obtained by farming§2 Rubber Trees§f. You should've got already an §2Rubber Sapling §ffrom Sifting§2 Dirt§f.

The §2Portable Cell§f is like an Backpack, so you can store in there Items you will need often like §2Tools§f but don't want to clutter your inventory with it everytime.

Note that it uses Energy and will lose some by the time you have it open, but don't worry it won't be long anymore till you can charge it!
It's finally time to make some §2LV Circuits§f! You will need ALOT of them, so it's recommend to already begin to batchcraft them so you don't need to craft them everytime again.
The next thing you will need is a§2 Machine Casing§f. You will need those in any Machine you want to craft and in other parts too like §2Hatches§f and §2Buses§f in Multiblocks.

It's finally time to make an §2Basic Steam Turbine§f and getting into §eAge 1 - Low Voltage Age§f!

The §2Steam Turbine§f will begin to produce Energy§f as soon as you feed it with §2Steam§f, but be sure to make enough §2Boilers§f as you will need ALOT to keep up now.

Time to make some §2LV Electric Motors§f! You will need this component alot as well now, so you should batch-craft them too!

NOTE: You can only make the §2Magnetic Iron Rod§f for now, so be sure to look at the second recipe in JEI.

The §2Steel Mesh §fis the third §a§fMesh you can obtain and allows you to obtain rarer Materials like §2§2Diamond§f and §2Graphite§e§e§f. 

You will need it in the LV age!

Welcome to §eAge 1 - Low Voltage§f! Now that you have got Electricity and Electric Machines, the real fun of Gregtech will begin!

Alot of things will be hard to understand if you play Gregtech for the first time, but will get alot easier as you begin to understand.

This Quest explains how §3Energy§2§f works in Gregtech.

Like in real life, you have§2 Amperage§f and §2Voltage§f. Each §2§3Tier §fhas an specific amount of §2Voltage§f that it can handle maximum. For example, §e§2§2§3§eULV §2§fhas an §2Voltage§f of 16 §3EU {Energy Units§f§3}§f§f per tick, so it§f can handle all recipes that take up to 16 §3Energy Units§f per tick. Anything above is §2§eLV§f, which can handle up to 32 §3Energy Units §fper tick and so on.
Each §2Cable§f also has an §3§2Voltage §floss per Block! Be sure to watch out for that!

§2Amperage§f§2 {Amps} §ftakes the §3Energy Units§f§f xN, where N is the number of §2Amps§f. Each §2§3Tier §fhas x4 §3§3§2Amps§f of the lower §4§3Tier§f.

NOTE: While you can power an §2§eLV §fMachine with an §2§eLV§f §2Cable§f that has §2Amps§f higher than 1, but you can't power it with an §eMV §f§2Cable§f, it will EXPLODE! This has the reason that the §2Cable§f of the corresponding §3Tier§f will only output as much §3§2Voltage§f as the Machine needs.

Gregtech has it's Machines divided in §3Tiers§f. Each Recipe in an Machine has an minimum §2§3Tier §fneeded to be able to be processed. 

There are 10 Tiers in Gregtech by standard:
§e0 - Ultra Low Voltage (ULV)
1 - Low Voltage (LV)
2 - Medium Voltage (MV)
3 - High Voltage (HV)
4 - Extreme Voltage (EV)
5 - Insane Voltage (IV)
6 - Ludicrious Voltage (LuV)
7 - Zero Point Module (ZPM)
8 - Ultimate Voltage (UV)
9 - Ultra High Voltage (UHV)

§eULV§f doesn't have any Machines.

§2§2§fYou may notice that §2§eSteam §fis not listed here, that has the reason that it is not directly an §3Tier§f on it's own and can perform all recipes that are §3§eLV§f.

§fUsing an higher §2§3§3Tier§f to process an Recipe with an lower §3Tier§f needed, the time of the Recipe gets halfed each time by how much the current §3Tier §fis greater than the §3Tier§f needed, so an §2§3§§§eLow Voltage§f Recipe in an §f§3§d§e§eHigh Voltage§f Machine have the time cut in half two times.

All §eGregTech§r Machines (except steam machines) can §a§e§f§r§1§2auto-output§r§r through their output face.  To enable §r§r§§auto-output§r, click the appropriate button in the GUI. Fluid and item auto-outputs are toggled separately. Further control over auto-outputs can be achieved with §eFilters§r and §eCovers§r, which are explained in the quest above this one.

§2Covers§r are placed by right-clicking with a cover in hand on a face of a machine, and removed with a §4§r§eCrowbar§r (or by mining the machine, but that's way slower).

Pretty much any §2GregTech§r machine will accept Covers, even if they wouldn't provide any functionality.

Opening a Cover is done by sneak-right-clicking it with an §eempty hand§r. You can also right-click with a §eScrewdriver§r, or sneak-right-click on another face using the grid.

For Covers that transfer Items/Fluids, you will have a button to enable/disable other forms of transfer through the cover.

§c- Disabled:§r only the cover will be allowed to transfer on this machine side.

§2- §2Allow Filtered (only relevant with a filter!):§r other transfer will be enabled only if it matches the filter.

§e- Allow Unfiltered:§r any other transfer is allowed on this machine side.

§2Covers§r works independently of §evoltage§r tiers, so placing a higher voltage cover on a lower voltage machine is §3safe§r, though higher tier covers gives §3faster transfer speeds§r.

The §eLathe§r is an important machine to help shape metals. Thanks to it, you can turn one §2Ingot§r into two §3Rods§&, and one §2Bolt§r into one §3screw.§r That's twice the efficiency on those recipes as opposed to crafting by hand.
the §eBending Machine§r unlocks the ability to convert one §2Ingot§r into one §3Plate§r, which is a better ratio than the Forge Hammer.

The Wiremill lets you make §etwo§r Wires from one Ingot. That should be three times cheaper than what you were doing up until now!

To the right of this Quest, you'll find some important machines which will grant you cheaper intermediates.

You will need a §eProgrammed Circuit§r for most recipes. Read the §eProgrammed Circuit§r for further details.

§2Note: Recipes inside §3LV Machines§r§2 go up to a maximum usage of §2§332 EU/t (LV)§r§2. Anything higher than that and you will need a §1§2§3§6§7§7§6MV§r§2 (or better) Machine. Needless to say, we aren't quite there yet.
§
§r

The §ePolarizer§r is one of the cheapest - if not the cheapest - §2LV§r machine. Use this to make §3Redstone-free Magnetic Rods§r for your Motors. Whenever you start to batch your Motors, this machine will save you stacks and stacks of Redstone.

§eSuperconductors§r are special Wires available for each Voltage tier. They don't come with a Cable counterpart, but that isn't necessary, as they have absolutely §2zero cable loss.§r

They also won't damage you when you touch them. This makes them the best choice for wiring, if not a little expensive in comparison to the other wires.

§2Note: You can't get the LV superconductor (Manganese Phosphide) until MV, so you're stuck with tin cables for now.§r

The §eLarge Boiler§o§r is an §3optional§r big-boy variant of the Small Boilers. Burning solid or liquid fuel and producing large amounts of steam, you have access to the §eLarge Bronze Boiler§r for now.

If you want Steam-based power production, this will be your first port-of-call. Other power options are listed in the §3MV§r chapter.

§4§cImportant:§r This Boiler §lCAN§r also §cexplode§r similarly to the regular Boilers! Usually, the explosion can be rather devastating... but it's configured to not damage blocks or entities in this modpack.


§b§3Water supply§r is §ecrucial§o.§§  Dedicate a §3Primitive Pump§r with a §3LV§r Output Hatch in the §6§c§b§2same chunk§o§r as the Boiler. Any biome will still be enough to supply enough water.

Once fully heated up, the §eLBB§r produces 800 Steam per tick, which is §e400EU/t§r after conversion, or 12.5 Basic Steam Turbines. Such (relatively!) immense power comes at the cost of §ca lot§r of burnable fuel.


§2With this in consideration§r, the GUI lets you §cthrottle§r the Boiler down to 25% power for less steam production in exchange for less fuel usage.

the §eBattery Buffer§r does nothing. However, if you place batteries inside its internal storage, it will act as a §2power buffer.

§r§eBattery Buffers§r handles §3two Amps in§o§r, and §2one Amp out§r, per Battery. The output side has the dot, and all other sides are used as inputs.

§2Note: You can also charge your tools directly inside the buffer!§r

The §eChemical Reactor§r will be required for §2§3§2A lot§r of recipes.

It can be used to make rubber at a §23x§r discount compared to the alloy smelter you have been using.

to get rubber sheets though, you will have to make a §eFluid solidifier§r, check the fluid solidifier quest for more details.

The §eFluid Solidifier§r turns §4§3Fluids§r into items, and needs a §2Mold§r to cast the fluid. It can be used to make §2§2§2Gears§r§r§r and §2§2§2Rotors§r§r§r more efficiently.

You can place your §eFluid Solidifer§r next to your §3Chemical Reactor§r to directly make 9 rubber sheets from 3 raw rubber pulp and 1 sulfur.

The §eAssembling Machine§r allows for better yields than your hand tools for things like §2vacuum tubes§r and §3resistors§r.

It is required to make §2Cupronickel coils§r, which is required for your next milestone, the §3Electric Blast Furnace§r.

The §eArc Furnace§r allows for easier recipes with §2Glass§r and §3Wrought Iron§r with a bit oxygen.

It be also be used to recycled machines into some of its original parts.

The §eElectric Blast Furnace§r is your first electric multiblock, congrats!

It can be used to smelt §2Aluminium dust §rinto §3Aluminium§r, the key material for §3Medium Voltage.§r 

This beefy boy eats up at least §3120EU/t§r, which means that you need §22 LV energy hatch§r to power it, along with at least §2§2§64 LV steam turbines.

§rAlong with the usual input and output bus, the blast furnace also needs a §3Muffler hatch§r and a §2Maintenance hatch.§r The muffler hatch must be placed at the middle of the top layer and §c

can not §rbe blocked by anyhting, the §2Maintenance hatch§r will be explained in the §dMaintenance§r quest.

Oxygen can be obtained from several methods:

§2- Centrifuging Air collected by a gas collector.§r

§2§3§2- Electrolysing silicon dioxide obtained from glass dust.

§rchoose whichever is the best for you.

Some multiblocks from now on requires §eMaintenance hatches.§r You will need to perform Maintenance for the Multiblock to begin operating those.

This is done by having a §3Wrench, a Screwdriver, a Soft Mallet, a Hammer, a Wire Cutter, and a Crowbar§r in your inventory, opening the Maintenance Hatch and §eclicking the center spot once§r. §cThere's no need to move tools individually.§r

Alternatively, you can circumvent these problems by placing a §3Tape§r in the Maintenance Hatch. Tape is gated behind some polymers starting from §1§3MV.§§r

Maintenance problems have a §35%§r chance of occuring every hour of multiblock activity. Needless to say, they are very rare. Each maintenance problem increases the recipe duration by §c10%§r, Fixing these problems is done the same way as above.

At §6HV§r, you'll unlock other Maintenance Hatches that do not require manual repairs.

Machines like the §eLV Alloy smelter§r are not shown here is because they are §cnot required§r as they do the same things as the steam counterparts and at the same speed.

§2Note: The LV extractor now can extract fluids compared to their steam counterparts.§r
These machines parts are required to craft §3LV§r machines, they also works as §2Covers§r themselves.
